          "source_html": "<div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Questions 27 - 33</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 1;\"><br/></p><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Look at the eight paragraphs (<strong>A – H</strong>). Which paragraph contains the following information?</p><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">You may choose any letter more than once.</p></div>\r\n    <div class=\"matrix-container\">\r\n        <table>\r\n            <thead><tr><th class=\"corner-header\">Question / Paragraph</th><th>A</th><th>B</th><th>C</th><th>D</th><th>E</th><th>F</th><th>G</th></tr></thead>\r\n            <tbody>\r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">27</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>27</strong><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑;\"> &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">the methods some companies use to try to keep their most creative employees</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_27\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_27\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_27\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_27\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_27\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_27\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_27\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：F</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词：methods；keep their most creative employees</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：F段，“giving more power to individuals in the company and setting up internal ideas-factories so that talents staff will not leave.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：原文提到要给公司里的个人更多的权力，建立内部的创意工厂，这样人才就不会离开，这是为了留住有创造力的员工。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：individuals in the company=employees, talents staff=creative employees</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">28</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>28</strong><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑;\"> &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">a new way of getting help with your personal difficulties</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_28\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_28\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_28\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_28\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_28\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_28\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_28\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：A</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词：new way；personal difficulties</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：A段，“…a team of 30 computer programmers are working on setting up websites that will allow subscribers to feed in details about themselves and their problems and to receive advice from &#39;virtual&#39; versions of personalities regarded as experts in their fields”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：原文提到一个团队正致力于建立一个网站，用户可以在网站上提供自己的问题，并从中获得建议。对应题目：这是一种帮助你解决个人困难的新方法。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：their problems=personal difficulties</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">29</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>29</strong><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑;\"> &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">how much investment goes into safeguarding the ideas of individuals</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_29\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_29\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_29\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_29\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_29\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_29\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_29\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：C</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词：Investment；safeguarding the ideas of individuals</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：C段，“ And a fortune is spent nowadays on identifying and protecting intellectual property: other people&#39;s ideas. According to the Pasadena-based Patent &amp; License Exchange in the United States, trading in intangible assets such as intellectual property rose from$15 billion in 1990 to $ 100 billion in 1998, with an increasing proportion of the rewards going to small firms and individuals.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：本题需要理解safeguarding the ideas of individuals，保护个人的思想就是保护知识产权，并且定位处举例了有关知识产权的证券交易，即为investment 。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：safeguarding the ideas of individuals=protecting intellectual property</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">30</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>30</strong><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑;\"> &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">two examples of companies which have succeeded through being innovative</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_30\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_30\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_30\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_30\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_30\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_30\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_30\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：B</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词：two examples of companies</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：B段，“Amazon (the internet bookstore) and Wal-Mart (the supermarket chain) which have produced completely new ideas or products that have changed their industries.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：原文提到了亚马逊和沃尔玛两家公司通过创新取得了成功。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：firm=company</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">31</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>31</strong><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑;\"> &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">how some innovators manage to avoid spending large sums of money on testing out their </span> &nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">ideas</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_31\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_31\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_31\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_31\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_31\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_31\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_31\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：E</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词：Innovator；testing out their ideas</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：E段，“Even in capital-intensive businesses such as pharmaceuticals, entrepreneurs can conduct profitable, early-stage research, selling out to the big firms when they reach expensive, risky clinical trials.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：本题原文定位比较困难 ，需要总结归纳。原文提到即使在资本密集型行业，如制药，企业家也可以进行有利可图的早期研究，当他们进入昂贵、高风险的临床试验时，将其出售给大公司。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：testing out their ideas=clinical trials</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">32</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>32</strong><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑;\"> &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">a commonly held opinion about product designers that needs to be proved wrong</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_32\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_32\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_32\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_32\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_32\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_32\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_32\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：G</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词：a commonly held opinion；product designers</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：G段，“Companies have to discredit the widespread view that jobs working on new products are for &#39;those who can&#39;t cope in the real business&#39;.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：原文定位句：人们普遍认为，开发新产品的工作是给“那些无法应付实际业务的人”做的，而企业必须改变（discredit）这种看法，说明该看法是错误的。Companies就是题目中的 product designers。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：a commonly held opinion=widespread view</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">33</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>33</strong><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑;\"> &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">the target of one large company that has changed its business focus</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_33\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_33\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_33\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_33\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_33\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_33\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_54391_33\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：F</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>定位关键词：target；business focus</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：F段，“Procter &amp; Gamble is now changing the entire direction of its business from global expansion to product development; one of its new aims is to get innovations accepted across the company.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：原文举例宝洁公司现在正把整个业务方向从全球扩张转向产品开发，表明business focus的转变，它的新目标之一是让整个公司接受创新。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：target=aim</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Questions 34 - 37</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 1;\"><br/></p><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">34</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Umagic Systems is an example of a new innovative company.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_34\" id=\"opt_34_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_34_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> TRUE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_34\" id=\"opt_34_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_34_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> FALSE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_34\" id=\"opt_34_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_34_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. TRUE</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>Q34, T</p><p>定位关键词：</p><p>Umagic Systems</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：</p><p>A段，“ Umagic Systems is a young firm and it’s hard to predict</p><p>how far they’ll go. In ten years&#39; time, consulting a computer</p><p>about your diet problems might seem natural or it might seem</p><p>absurd. But the company and others like it are beginning to</p><p>seriously worry large American firms, who see such half-crazy</p><p>new and innovative ideas as a threat to their own future success.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：</p><p>原文提到Umagic Systems是一家年轻的公司，但它开始让</p><p>美国的大公司感到担忧，他们认为这种半疯狂的新创意会</p><p>威胁到他们自己未来的成功，即说明Umagic Systems</p><p>是一家新的创新型公司。</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">35</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Amazon and Wal-Mart have exchanged successful ideas on innovation.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_35\" id=\"opt_35_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_35_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> TRUE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_35\" id=\"opt_35_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_35_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> FALSE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_35\" id=\"opt_35_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_35_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. NOT GIVEN</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>Q35, NG</p><p>定位关键词：</p><p>Amazon；Wal-Mart</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：</p><p>B段，“Amazon (the internet bookstore) and Wal-Mart</p><p>(the supermarket chain) which have produced completely</p><p>new ideas or products that have changed their industries.”</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>解析：</p><p>原文提到亚马逊和沃尔玛提出了全新的想法或产品，改变了</p><p>他们所在的行业，但并未提到两者之间交换了在创新方面的想法。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">36</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Using financial rewards to encourage innovation is an outdated practice.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> TRUE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> FALSE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. FALSE</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>Q36, F</p><p>定位关键词：</p><p>financial rewards；outdated practice</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：</p><p>G段，“They have to change the culture by introducing hard</p><p>incentives, such as giving more generous bonuses to those</p><p>who come up with successful new ideas and, particularly,</p><p>not punishing those whose experiments fail.”</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>解析：</p><p>原文提到要用更多奖金奖励那些提出成功新想法的人，并且不惩罚实验失败的人，这是一种激励（incentives），并不是过时做法。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：</p><p>financial rewards=bonuses</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">37</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>IBM failed to understand David Post&#39;s &#39;virtual experts&#39; idea.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> TRUE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> FALSE</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. TRUE</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>Q37, T</p><p>定位关键词：</p><p>IBM；David Post；virtual experts</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：</p><p>H段，“He also recalls with glee the looks of total</p><p>incomprehension when he tried to sell his &#39;virtual</p><p>experts&#39; idea three years ago to firms such IBM,</p><p>though, as he cheerfully adds, &#39;of course, they could</p><p>have been right.&#39; ”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：</p><p>原文指出人们无法理解David Post ‘virtual experts&#39; 的想法，</p><p>举例IBM这家公司，与题目符合 。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：</p><p>incomprehension=fail to understand</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Questions 38-40</strong></p><p style=\"line-height: 1;\"><br/></p><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Choose the correct answer.</p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">38</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What point does the writer make about intellectual property?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> It can be lost when firms merge.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> It tends to belong to companies rather than individuals.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> It is valued more than it used to be.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> It is not usually owned by small companies.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. It is valued more than it used to be.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>Q38, C</p><p>定位关键词：</p><p>Intellectual property</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：</p><p>C段，“ And a fortune is spent nowadays on identifying and</p><p>protecting intellectual property: other people&#39;s ideas.</p><p>According to the Pasadena-based Patent &amp; License Exchange</p><p>in the United States, trading in intangible assets such as</p><p>intellectual property rose from$15 billion in 1990 to $ 100 billion</p><p>in 1998, with an increasing proportion of the rewards going to</p><p>small firms and individuals.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：</p><p>原文通过举例位于帕萨迪纳的美国专利与许可交易所</p><p>(Patent &amp; License Exchange)的数据，知识产权等</p><p>无形资产的交易从1990年的150亿美元上升到1998年的</p><p>1000亿美元，其中越来越多的回报流向了小公司和个人，</p><p>以此表明知识产权比之前更加重要。</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">39</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Peter Chemin is an example of someone who has realized that</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> large companies are less innovative than small ones.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> other businesses are more innovative than the film business.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> his employees need more experience of innovation.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> he is the best person to encourage innovation.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. large companies are less innovative than small ones.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>Q39, A</p><p>定位关键词：</p><p>Peter Chemin</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：</p><p>D段，“In the management of creativity, size is your enemy,&#39;</p><p>argues Peter Chemin, who runs Fox TV and film empire for</p><p>News Corporation. &#39;One person managing 20 movies is never</p><p>going to be as involved as one doing five movies. &#39;He has</p><p>thus tried to break down the studio into smaller units, even</p><p>at the risk of incurring higher costs.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：</p><p>原文中，Peter Chemin 认为在创意管理方面，规模是敌人，</p><p>一个管理20部电影的人永远不会像一个管理5部电影的人</p><p>那样投入并且试图将工作室拆分成更小的单元。他的想法和</p><p>做法就表明大公司的创新能力不如小公司，选A。没有指出</p><p>其他行业比电影行业更有创新力，排除B。C、D并未体现。</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">40</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>In conclusion, the writer suggests that</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> computer-based industries cannot be innovative.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> big firms are right to be cautious about innovation.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> small firms should not worry about early failures.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> innovation will always involve some uncertainty.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> D. innovation will always involve some uncertainty.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>Q40, D</p><p><br/></p><p>原文：</p><p>H段，“David Post, the founder of Umagic, isn&#39;t so sure:</p><p>&#39;The only successful intrapreneurs are ones who leave and</p><p>become entrepreneurs.&#39;”</p><p><br/></p><p>解析：</p><p>题目问最后作者的建议，即定位到最后一段，原文提到David Post</p><p>的观点回答了本段第一个问句：唯一成功的内部创业者是那些离开</p><p>公司去创业的人。后面还提到当时人们完全不理解他&#39;virtual experts&#39;</p><p>的想法的经历，以及计算机无法告诉你要怎么去做，表明创新总是</p><p>包含很多不确定因素的。</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div>",
